&lt;p&gt;Redwood Software delivers powerful automation solutions that simplify and accelerate critical business and IT processes for some of the world’s largest enterprises. The Redwood Automation Platform streamlines complex business workflows and operations, reduces manual effort, ensures compliance, and accelerates business outcomes through intelligent, cloud-native automation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Director of Engineering, you are the accountable owner of the products and services chartered to our Netherlands Engineering Hub, reporting to the Vice President of Engineering. You will provide decisive leadership, establish clear operating standards, and ensure the consistent delivery of high-quality, enterprise-grade software aligned with Redwood’s strategic priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role carries full responsibility for execution, technical direction, delivery predictability, and team performance within the Netherlands hub. You will build and sustain a culture where commitments are met, outcomes are owned, and excellence is the baseline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are not only a people leader — you are the operational authority for the hub’s output, health, and performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success in this role requires a relentless focus on results, measurable impact, and continuous improvement. You will set a high bar for accountability and ensure that teams deliver on their commitments with discipline, transparency, and urgency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Redwood, our Software Development Lifecycle is AI-embedded and AI-first. You will be responsible for evangelizing and operationalizing AI across the entire development process — from ideation and architecture through coding, testing, release, diagnostics, and continuous improvement. AI adoption is not optional; it is a leadership mandate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hub Leadership&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the technical and operational outcomes of the Netherlands Engineering Hub.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish clear accountability for roadmap delivery, quality, reliability, and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and enforce measurable KPIs around delivery predictability, cycle time, defect rates, and operational health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure commitments made to Product and executive leadership are delivered — or transparently escalated with mitigation plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive a culture where teams “Own the Outcome” and operate with autonomy, urgency, and clarity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Results-Driven Execution&lt;/p&gt;

